or, and the implications of this behavior for their families and the broader society. The book's narrative of the faithful maiden cult interweaves late imperial political, cultural, social and intellectual history, thus, providing a new window onto the history of the late imperial period.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Nov 2020) 0aSingle womenxHistoryxChina. 0aSingle womenxSocial conditionsxChina. 0aSingle womenzChinaxHistory. 0aSingle womenzChinaxSocial conditions. 0aYoung womenxHistoryxChina. 0aYoung womenxSocial conditionsxChina. 0aYoung womenzChinaxHistory. 0aYoung womenzChinaxSocial conditions. 7aHISTORY / Asia / China.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804786782zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804786782423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804786782.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles